13:
Of course not. There is still much to
be done.
15:
Command the enforcers, terminate
the enemy forces, and, well...
20: ...I shall leave her in your hands.
23: You don't gotta tell me twice.
27:
Let's go, guys. It's almost time for the
main event.
32: I see you've made it this far.
35: I made you a promise, didn't I?
38:
Fool. If you hadn't come here, I
would have let you continue living
free.
40:
And you otherworlders, as well. If
you had just left and gone back to
your worlds...
44:
Sorry, but we don't plan on cutting
our journey short just yet. Let us
through.
48:
It's about time that you two made
up.
55:
Why are fools all so eager to rush to
their demise?
58:
Very well. I'll humor your foolishness
before making you drones of my
very own.
60:
All of your senses, thoughts, and
emotions shall be at the mercy of
the eternal night. Just like it always
has been.
63:
WHY does it have to be that way
though?
68:
I know you don't mean that. You just
haven't realized it yet.
79:
I mean, it was fun working together,
right?
86:
You and me, the dynamic duo of
Qualia City.
88:
Forget the rules of this wack
dystopia. All I want is to see the
sky—together with you.
90:
And once we do that, we could hit
up a café and shoot the breeze.
Wouldn't that be nice?
93:
Just two friends, out on the night. I
don't care about bringing things
back to the way they were.
Tomorrow's another day, right?
102:
I don't need you... I don't need any of
you!
104:
I'll admit this, Bulleta. You actually
gave me hope—even if only for a
second.
106:
Which is why I'm breaking ties with
you here and now. Goodbye...
forever.
111:
Why do you have to be like this?! I
know this isn't what you really want!
118:
Don't you get it? I am the living
symbol of this corporation—the light
of this neon skyline that will forever
burn into the night!
121:
It doesn't matter what my heart
desires. I can only continue to be as
I am now!
124:
Says who?! The only one that should
decide what you want is you!
127: So just say the word, and I'm there!
134:
All limiters disengaged. Power
output: maximum!
141:
I'll destroy it all—everything before
me and everything I've ever felt! This
is how it must be, Bulleta!
145:
Fine! But just so you know, I don't
break that easily!
147:
I know you're hurting, somewhere
deep inside... I'm gonna show you
that damned sky—or die trying!
150:
This freedom blaster's locked and
loaded, Love! I'll use whatever
ammunition I need to get through to
the real you!
153:
And I'll clip your wings of freedom
and imprison you in the cocoon of
my despair!
